@dev We use COOPToken (ERC20 based OpenZeppelin implementation) address to instatiate this contract inside SmartCOOP and to call
 transfer function from within depositFruitsToCoop function. Then we use chanilink Kovan test net address to instatiate interface which
 will provide to us real time ETH/USD price feed.
 IMPORTANT: if we deploy this contract localy get_contract and get_acount funcitons from scripts/helpful_scripts.py will notice that we
 are deploying localy and instead of chainlink Kovan test net interface we will deploy mock to be used in context od local enviroment.
 What means that there is no need for any additional intervention or configuration from side of developer. This contract will be fully
 operational in Kovan testnet enviroment as well as in local ganache dev enviroment with Chainlink price feed.

@dev This function is used to block usage of becomeCoopMember, depositFruitsToCOOP and bid functions in case of bugs or hacks. Pause function
 can be called only by EOA who deploy COOPTOkena and SmartCOOP and it is inherited from OpenZeppelin Pausable smart contract.
@dev This function is used to unpause usage of becomeCoopMember, deposit FruitsToCOOP and bid functions.

becomeCoopMember().notice: Allowing new EOA to become SmartCOOP member

returns._0: If execution was successful function will return true

bid(uint256).details: RASPBERRY_PRICE is hard coded because there is no out of the box chainlink date feed for raspberry price and alterantive solution includes using HTTP GET request to external API using chainlink request&receive data cycle. What we consider to be a bit out of scope of this project and inital ambition.
bid(uint256).notice: This function will allow any EOA that is not already member of cooperative to bid for fruits inside SmartCOOP warhouse.

params._amount: uint256 for amount of fruits bidder would like to buy

returns._0: If execution was successful function will return true

constructor.details: We use COOPToken (ERC20 based OpenZeppelin implementation) address to instatiate this contract inside SmartCOOP and to call transfer function from within depositFruitsToCoop function. Then we use chanilink Kovan test net address to instatiate interface which will provide to us real time ETH/USD price feed. IMPORTANT: if we deploy this contract localy get_contract and get_acount funcitons from scripts/helpful_scripts.py will notice that we are deploying localy and instead of chainlink Kovan test net interface we will deploy mock to be used in context od local enviroment. What means that there is no need for any additional intervention or configuration from side of developer. This contract will be fully operational in Kovan testnet enviroment as well as in local ganache dev enviroment with Chainlink price feed.

depositFruitsToCOOP(uint256).notice: Allowing EOA which already pay SmartCOOP membership fee to deposit fruits to SmartCOOP warehouse

params._kg: Passing number of kilograms producer would like to deposit to warehouse

returns._0: If execution was successful function will return true

ethUSD(uint256).notice: Used for calculating amount of wei from USD total

params._amount: Price in USD which should be converetd to wei

returns._0: Amount of wei to be payed

getBidderAccountBalance(address).notice: This function is used to provide overview of bidder SmartCOOP account

returns._0: If executed successfully function will return 2 values: 1) total payed for all goods bidder bought; 2) Total amount of kg bidder bought

getLatestPrice().details: In case we deploy contracts to local dev enviroment get_contract and get_acount fuctions from scripts/helpful_scripts.py will deploy mock contract to be used in context of local dev. enviroment. In case we deploy to Kovan test net same function will deploy adequte contracts (KOvan testnet) and use proper accounts for this purpose.
getLatestPrice().notice: This function is used to get ETH/USD price ration from Chainlink price data feed. This return value form this function is later used to calculate how much bidder needs to pay for fruits he bought from SmartCOOP .

returns._0: This function returns price (int256 data type) provided by Chainlink price date feed

getUserAccountBalance(address).notice: This function is used to provide overview of user SmartCOOP account

params._user: We pass user address as argument

returns._0: If executed sucesfully function will return 3 values: 1) how much user pay SmartCOOP fee; 2) Total //..//// amount of kg user currenly have in SmartCOOP warehouse; 3) Total amount of COOPTokens he/she receive

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pause().details: This function is used to block usage of becomeCoopMember, depositFruitsToCOOP and bid functions in case of bugs or hacks. Pause function can be called only by EOA who deploy COOPTOkena and SmartCOOP and it is inherited from OpenZeppelin Pausable smart contract.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unpause().details: This function is used to unpause usage of becomeCoopMember, deposit FruitsToCOOP and bid functions.

withdraw().details: By modifier onlyOwner we restrict right to call this function only to EOA who deploy both SmartCOOP and COOPToken
withdraw().notice: This function is used to withdraw eth from SmartCOOP account

returns._0: If execution was successful function will return true
